# AWS-0104: Security group rule allows unrestricted egress to any IP address.
# Justification: EKS Nodes require outbound access to reach public container registries (ECR, DockerHub) 
# and AWS APIs. In a future iteration, this will be hardened using VPC Endpoints and a private registry.
# --- Infrastructure / Network ---
AVD-AWS-0104 # Unrestricted egress - Required for node bootstrap
AWS-0104     # (Legacy ID) Unrestricted egress

# --- Toolchain / Docker ---
DS-0002 # Root user - Required for runner compatibility
DS-0026 # Healthcheck - Not applicable for CLI containers
DS-0010 # apt-get recommends - Toolchain optimization

# --- Global / Upstream Noise ---
AVD-AWS-0105 # NACL allows all ports - Default module behavior
AVD-AWS-0040 # EKS public access - Dev environment requirement
AVD-AWS-0041 # EKS public CIDR - Dev environment requirement
AVD-AWS-0038 # EKS public endpoint - Dev environment requirement
AVD-AWS-0039 # EKS encryption - Learning environment simplification
AVD-AWS-0088 # S3 Encryption - Learning environment simplification
